Mennel Milling Co. has performed a hazard evaluation for the chlorination processes at the facility.  As a result of this evaluation, several changes are planned to improve safety.  These changes, to be implemented by the end of 1999, include (but are not limited to) the following:
Establishment of a procedure to minimize the potential for accidents during unloading of full chlorine containers;
Interlocking of flour agitator motors with the auto cabinet ball valve such that the valve will close and stop the flow of chlorine gas in the event of an agitator motor cut out;
Installation of sleeve or other protective cover for chlorine line between the new chlorine room and the mill;
Installation of a remote on/off switch for the chlorine cabinet automatic valve to allow the flow of chlorine to be stopped remotely.
